---
import Layout from "../components/Layout.astro";
import Heading from "../components/Heading.astro";
import Prose from "../components/Prose.astro";
import Finis from "../components/Finis.astro";
---

<Layout title="About - Ariel Messing">
  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "AboutPage",
    "name": "About Ariel Messing",
    "description": "About Ariel Messing.",
    "url": new URL("/about", Astro.site).href,
    "isPartOf": {
      "@type": "WebSite",
      "name": "Ariel Messing",
      "url": Astro.site?.href,
    },
  })} />
  
  <section class="about">
    <header class="about-header">
      <Heading as="h1">About</Heading>
    </header>
    <Prose>
      <p>
        For the last twenty years, I have been exploring the craft of software development. 
      </p>
      <p>
        What started with an early interest in Mathematics and Computer Science has become a long-term focus on how complex systems are built and maintained: a balance between the discipline of architectural design and the broader, occasionally more chaotic, landscape of engineering — the whole, and the artisan's eye for the individual line of code.
      </p>
      <p>
        A few years ago, a move to the UK with my wife coincided with the start of the pandemic. That period of forced stoicism in a quiet Kentish village served as an invitation to return to hands-on coding. From machine learning to generative art via the patient nature of open-source contribution, it was a chance to explore corners of computing I had previously left untouched.
      </p>
      <p>
        Before transitioning to freelance work, I was enjoying the mix of high-level vision with practical reality as a developer, and later systems architect and product manager for a cyber security startup through two successive acquisitions. A personal highlight of those years was the core data flow redesign, born of the pressure of scale, as a serverless solution — leading the team transforming a fragile prototype into a resilient, production environment.
      </p>
      <p>
        When not at my desk, I might be unravelling a thread of Central European history, tending to a sourdough babka, or cycling through the English countryside.
      </p>
    </Prose>
    <Finis />
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: var(--width-content);
  }

  .about-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }
</style>